  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddCmd
    Represents the data type containing information to add a new command to the data packet processing visitor.
    MyCitySelMsg
    a message representing city selections it contains a list of cities avaliable
    MyCitySelMsgCmd
    only used for testing unknown data packet and cmd2ModelAdapter cmd that only process datapacket of MyCitySelMsg one instance of this class is sent upon request
    MyGameStatusMsg
    a game status message containing a string that will describe game status in a proper manner
    MyGameStatusMsgCmd  
    MyMapFrameMsg
    a class containing a java awt Component usually containing an empty jframe, and set up all other components in the cmd that process this frame.
    MyMapFrameMsgCmd
    cmd that processes mapframmsg by adding mappanel and buttons, layer of annotation with action listeners that will send back datapacket of certain type to the server Iuser, so that the player could communicate back to server.
    MyStringMsg
    class used for communication between client and game server itself is a data of String
    MyStringMsgCmd
    cmd of processing string msg.
    MyToggleAnnotation
    subclass of ToggleAnnotation in the map package the only difference is when someone clicking this annotation, besides change text on the annotation.
    StatusFail
    concrete class of IStatusfail which says a datapacket is failed to be processed
    StatusOk
    concrete class of IStatusfail which says a datapacket is ok to be processed
    TextMessage
    A data type that encapsulates a text message Implementations should be associated with the host ID ITextMessage.class
